content.text:
The `if` statement checks if a condition is true. If the condition is true (`1`), the code inside the `if` block runs. Otherwise, it’s skipped. The syntax is:
```c
if (condition) {
  // Code runs here if the condition is true
}
```

The `else` statement provides an alternative block of code to run if the `if` condition is false. It always follows an `if` and can’t be used alone. The syntax is:
```c
if (condition) {
  // Runs if condition is true
} else {
  // Runs if condition is false
}
```

The `else if` statement checks additional conditions if the first `if` is false. It allows testing multiple conditions in sequence. The syntax is:
```c
if (condition1) {
  // Runs if condition1 is true
} else if (condition2) {
  // Runs if condition2 is true
} else {
  // Runs if no conditions are true
}
```

